The Adamawa state government has declared 3-days mourning for the late paramount ruler Hamma Bachama, Homun Stephen Irimiya who died at the age 66 years. Governor Ahmadu Fintiri gave the directive in a statement issued by his press secretary, Mr Humwashi Wonosikou, on Monday in Yola. According to the statement, the official mourning takes immediate effect from Monday, June 29 to Wednesday, July 1. “Consequently, all flags should be flown at half-mast across the state from today Monday, June 29 to July 1. “The official mourning is in memory of late paramount leader, Hama Bachama, Honest Stephen, who passed away on in the early hours of Sunday in Numan,’’ the statement read in part. The paramount ruler, who ascented the throne in December 2012 died, died yesterday after a brief illness. The late Irimiya the 28th ruler of the Bachama kingdom, was buried yesterday in Lamurde. 